<p><b>Hans Christian Andersen</b> (pronounced <span title="Pronunciation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">[ˈhanˀs ˈkʰʁæʂd̥jan ˈɑnɐsn̩]</a></span> in Danish), also known as simply <b>H. C. Andersen</b> <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[hɔse ˈɑnɐsn̩]</span>); (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1805-04-02"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="04-02"><a href="/wiki/April_2" title="April 2">April 2</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1805" title="1805">1805</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1875-08-04"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="08-04"><a href="/wiki/August_4" title="August 4">August 4</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1875" title="1875">1875</a></span>) was a <a href="/wiki/Denmark" title="Denmark">Danish</a> <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">author</a> and <a href="/wiki/Poet" title="Poet">poet</a>, most famous for his <a href="/wiki/Fairy_tale" title="Fairy tale">fairy tales</a>. Among his best-known stories are "<a href="/wiki/The_Steadfast_Tin_Soldier" title="The Steadfast Tin Soldier">The Steadfast Tin Soldier</a>", "<a href="/wiki/The_Snow_Queen" title="The Snow Queen">The Snow Queen</a>", "<a href="/wiki/The_Little_Mermaid" title="The Little Mermaid">The Little Mermaid</a>", "<a href="/wiki/Thumbelina" title="Thumbelina">Thumbelina</a>", "<a href="/wiki/The_Little_Match_Girl" title="The Little Match Girl">The Little Match Girl</a>", "<a href="/wiki/The_Ugly_Duckling" title="The Ugly Duckling">The Ugly Duckling</a>" and "<a href="/wiki/The_Red_Shoes_(fairy_tale)" title="The Red Shoes (fairy tale)">The Red Shoes</a>". During Andersen's lifetime he was feted by royalty and acclaimed for having brought joy to children across Europe. His fairy tales have been translated into over 150 languages and continue to be published in millions of copies all over the world and inspired many other works.<sup id="cite_ref-EB_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EB-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
